    },
    {
        "Nile": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nile"
    },
    {
        ".": null
    },
    {
        "His debt to previous authors of prose \"histories\" might be questionable, but there is no doubt that Herodotus owed much to the example and inspiration of poets and story-tellers. For example, Athenian tragic poets provided him with a world-view of a balance between conflicting forces, upset by the ": null
    },
    {
        "hubris": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubris"
    },
    {
        " of kings, and they provided his narrative with a model of episodic structure. His familiarity with Athenian tragedy is demonstrated in a number of passages echoing ": null
    },
    {
